      <!-- Best Time to Visit -->
      <section class="section" id="best-time">
        <h2>Best Time to Visit</h2>
        <div class="desc">
          Budapest unfolds differently each season: spring breathes life into riverside walks, summer brings open-air concerts and long golden light, autumn colors the hills and cools the baths, and winter makes the steaming pools feel like small miracles. There’s no single “best” time—every visit has its texture. If it’s your first time, aim for late spring (May–June) or early autumn (September–October): the weather is gentle, crowds are moderate, and the city feels both vivid and unhurried. 
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="max-width:850px; margin:0 auto; display:flex; gap:20px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
